登.definition: to scale (a height); to ascend; to mount; to publish or record; to enter (e.g. in a register); to press down with the foot; to step or tread on; to put on (shoes or trousers) (dialect); to be gathered and taken to the threshing ground (old)

登上.definition: to climb over; to ascend onto; to mount

登仙.definition: to become immortal; big promotion; die

登入.definition: to log in (to a computer); to enter (data)

登出.definition: to log out (computer); to publish; to be published; to appear (in a newspaper etc)

登堂入室.definition: lit. from the main room, enter the inner chamber (idiom); fig. to go to the next level; to attain a higher level

登場.definition: to go on stage; fig. to appear on the scene; used in advertising to mean new product

登封市.definition: Dengfeng, county-level city in Zhengzhou 鄭州市|郑州市[Zheng4zhou1 Shi4], Henan

登山.definition: to climb a mountain; climbing; mountaineering

登峰.definition: to climb a mountain; to scale a peak; mountain climbing; mountaineering

登峰造極.definition: to reach great heights (in technical skills or scholastic achievements)

登徒子.definition: Master Dengtu, a famous historical lecherous character; lecher; skirt-chaser

登機手續櫃檯.pinyin: dēng jī shǒu xù guì tái

登機橋.definition: boarding gate (at airport); aircraft boarding bridge

登臨.definition: to visit places famous for their scenery

登記名.definition: to register one's name; account name (on a computer)

登載.definition: to publish (in newspapers or magazines); to record (bookkeeping entries)

登陸.definition: to land; to come ashore; to make landfall (of typhoon etc); to log in (frequently used erroneous variant of 登錄|登录[deng1 lu4])

登頂.definition: (lit. and fig.) to get to the top

登高一呼.definition: to make a clarion call; to make a public appeal

登高望遠.definition: to stand tall and see far (idiom); taking the long and broad view; acute foresight
